Description: Employee Attendance Software
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, Silicon Valley, West Coast
Full Description: Zarlu is an employee time & attendance tracking software application. Employees can submit schedule changes and businesses can manage employee schedule changes. Every employee of a business receives a Zarlu account. Members of a organization who do not approve co-workers' time off are designated employees. Employees are able to submit time off, view approved or rejected time off requests, schedule events with their personal calendar, view a history of time off requests and their schedule changes, and personalize their account with a photo. By giving each employee the ability to manage their own schedule, Zarlu streamlines the attendance process for managers by eliminating the need to manually enter their co-workers time off requests and schedule changes. Any employee in your business who approves or rejects other co-worker attendance requests is designated as a manager in Zarlu. A manager can view their employees’ time off history, manage accrual totals and accrual rates, customize Zarlu’s attendance rules to fit their business’s guidelines, view charts of how employees are using leave, and much more. A manager in addition to their managerial features has full access to the same features as employees, which allows for businesses with hierarchies to structure their approval process in Zarlu.

Description: Feminspire is an online publication featuring a global collection of female voices.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Los Angeles Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Feminspire is an online publication featuring a global collection of female voices. They are a platform for women to share their thoughts on social issues, feminism, politics, culture, beauty, fashion, and everything in between. Feminspire came into existence from the realization that there is an enormous and disturbing amount of female negativity on the internet. With so many messages that range from demeaning to judgmental to exploitative, their mission is to create a media website that speaks directly to women and with them in mind. What makes Feminspire unique is that their content is driven exclusively by female contributors. They know their audience because they are their audience (seriously – not only do they write for Feminspire, but they enjoy reading it, too). Their goal is to give women a place in the media where they can speak up and have their voices heard. A note about intersectionality: Feminspire was created by a white woman living in America, and many (although not all) of their staff members are white women and women who live in Western countries. They don’t claim to be able to represent all women within their content, but they strive to do the best they can. Inclusivity and intersectionality are two of their most important goals as a website, and it’s their hope that you’ll be able to find something here that resonates with you.

Whether you have experienced a major flood, or just some minor damage, all of our cleanup and restoration work is guaranteed to be of the best quality. Description: Rocky Mountain Oasis has combined the retreat center with the conference center and addressed the weaknesses of both.
Headquarters Regions: Western US
Full Description: The leadership in North American churches and business are in trouble.  Leaders are severely over-worked and under-appreciated.  Severe burn out and career changes are a result.  Retreat facilities and conference centers are two things that are used to attempt to combat this ever growing problem.  However, both are inadequate on their own.  Retreat centers offer short term escape from the reality of everyday life; but reality still exists after returning from the retreat.  Conference centers teach attendees how to handle problems; but the solutions learned are nearly always conceptual and do not address the specific problems of the attendee. Rocky Mountain Oasis has combined the retreat center with the conference center and addressed the weaknesses of both.  An oasis is a place to escape the deadliness of the desert and to become refreshed and equipped to continue the remainder of the journey.  So is Rocky Mountain Oasis.  The Rocky Mountain Oasis experience begins with the oasis on the horizon.  We invite specific leadership teams to our facility and customize their experience so that they receive precisely the escape, the rejuvenation, and the tools they need to be able to go back out into life and complete the journey.  This begins with pre-stay interviews and preparations, continues with a time of retreat and conference at our facility, and culminates with post-stay follow-up and encouragement.  The Rocky Mountain Oasis experience ends when the leadership team has reached the edge of the desert and no longer needs nurturing or encouragement. Our owners (Joe & Kathy McCarn, and Sharon Stoeber) have spent the past eleven years (and perhaps their entire lives) preparing for this endeavor.  With the right experience, contacts, and education, we are now prepared to help others to reach more of their potential.
Founders: Joe McCarn, Kathy McCarn, Sharon Stoeber

Full Description: Critihost They have helped build and maintain various websites and web-based applications. Along the way, a focus was always put on reliability, scalability, and of course performance. When starting, they used shared hosting similar to what they now offer. Along the way, they realized that all the hosts had issues, related to overcrowded servers and cutting corners. Companies were so caught up in growing quickly that the focus was never where it should be, the customer. The logical choice was to move to run their dedicated servers. They chose a good network connection and hardware. The changes were immediate and their customers were much happier as a result. Their focus is currently on shared website hosting but they can, and do, accommodate everything from the personal site to multi-server enterprise-grade operations. If have a project in mind and need hosting, guidance, or development and design don’t be afraid to contact us. Description: Asternotes is a cloud-based mobile platform that caters to the needs of consumers and storeowners.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Phoenix Area, Western US
Full Description: Asternotes meets the mobile needs felt by consumers and store owners in the thrift, resale and secondhand marketplaces. ABOUT: Asternotes is the new cloud-based thrift and resale shoppers’ mobile platform serving both thrift shoppers and brick-and-mortar thrift shops and resale store owners. Asternotes’ all-in-one mobile app suite helps serious thrift shoppers conveniently use their smart phones to make money, save money and help our planet in their local brick-and-mortar thrift stores and resale shops.  The eco-friendly mobile app now offers mobile couponing and marketing for thrift shop owners on its mobile platform.   INDUSTRY:  There are approx. 25,000 resale stores in the US and it is an approx. $13 billion in annual revenues industry according to NARTS with the number of stores within the industry growing about 7% a year.  Thrift and resale is a multi-billion dollar a year proven industry and that’s due in large part to dedicated resale consumers, many of whom do not leave home without their smart phones.   In addition, thrift shopping in local brick-and-mortar thrift shops and resale stores positively impacts the lives of millions of people because it reduces used textiles in landfills, making earth better for all of us.  UNIQUE INTERSECTIONS: Mobile, thrift, local, eco-friendly, social, photos, messaging, recommendations, couponing  BENEFITS AND FEATURES FOR THE CONVENIENCE OF COMMUNITY MEMBERS: -Asternotes is designed specifically as a thrift shopper’s mobile app. It has all the features a serious thrift shopper could ever want without having to tap in and out of different apps all over your mobile phone: -3rd insight resale recommendations (algorithm-based) -Photos for sharing discoveries -10-second video clips for sharing discoveries -Private resale option to asterbuddies within the network -Private Messaging -Location-based thrift directory -Nudge research reminder -Inventory management of your thrift discoveries -Create Personal or Hot Items thrift shopping lists -Send/Receive pick up or pass up votes on  thrift finds -Folders for sorting your thrift treasures  -one-click mapping from your personal calendar to direct you on the best route to save gas & time based on locations entered in your calendar  -Mobile coupons from Asternotes’ thrift store network in a special section (no annoying popups) BENEFITS AND FEATURES FOR THRIFT AND RESALE STORE OWNERS/MANAGERS: -Asternotes’ Asterdeals helps thrift and resale brands engage with mobile customers through a relevant mobile marketing platform allowing thrift shops and resale stores to execute and manage local, relevant coupon marketing. -An effective, cost-saving, cloud-based markdown and promotion management system for mobile- THE ASTERNOTES MOBILE APP IS NOT REQUIRED TO UTILIZE THE SYSTEM      -Targeted, relevant mobile platform exclusive to thrift and resale consumers -Self-serve web portal -Easy to use  -Top of mobile screen exposure -Location-based -Brand awareness with logos/pics, colors  -Preview mobile ad coupons and banners on the Aster*Phone simulator on-line  -Mobile Coupon option of text, bar codes or QR codes -QR code and bar code generator at no extra cost -Mobile Coupons shareable on social media -No hardware costs -No set-up cost -helps for-profit and not-for-profit thrift shops and resale stores -Big and small thrift and resale stores can now make mobile advertising campaigns part of their business plan today -Reduce or eliminate current flyer and advertising paper/ink/printing costs FOUNDERS:       Asternotes was founded by Ronda Polhill, thrift shopping expert and author of The R.E.L.I.C.S. Thrift Shopping Method (kindle) and Shalayne Kemp, the sole android developer who used her technical skills to integrate numerous APIs into the complex Asternotes mobile app platform.       Polhill hopes free downloads of the Asternotes’ app encourages sustainable shopping, inspires users to shop local thrift stores more often and reduces used, recyclable clothing in landfills. Asternotes is free to download at googleplay.com.  The iOS version is coming soon.
